This paper deals with the computational complexity of a graph problem related to minor models, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper heavily relies on graph theory and algorithms, which are also relevant to computer graphics (cs.CG), data structures (cs.DS), and theoretical computer science (cs.CC). Additionally, the paper uses techniques such as treewidth modulators and bidimensionality, which are common in the study of graph theory and combinatorial optimization (cs.GT).
